title: Salmon

title: Shrimp
description: Shrimp is a versatile, low-calorie seafood that provides iodine, phosphorus, zinc, and magnesium. Shrimps are vital for many reasons.

title: Tilapia
description: Tilapia is high in vitamin B12, which helps your body make DNA, maintain its nervous system, and produce red blood cells.

title: Herring
description: Herring has a higher omega-3 content than sardines, trout and mackerel. It's also an excellent source of vitamin D and selenium.

title: Lamb Meat.
description: Lamb Meat is rich source of high-quality protein, vitamins and minerals, including iron, zinc, and vitamin B12. It also helps to prevent anemia.

title: Goat Meat.
description: Goat meat is low in saturated fats and has more of the recommended unsaturated fats. Goat meat also has lower levels of cholesterol compared to other meats.

title: Rabbit Meat
description: Rabbit meats are recognized as the excellent sources of iron, B12 and protein that keeps us healthy by building and repairing our muscles, skin and blood.

title: Beef
description: Beef is naturally rich in protein, which helps muscle growth and supports muscle mass. It provides iron and vitamins (niacin, riboflavin, vitamins B6 and B12).

title: Vegetarian Diet
description: It has vitamins C and E, dietary fiber, folic acid, potassium, magnesium, and phytochemicals (plant chemicals), such as carotenoids and flavonoids.
